    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - ENGINE ELECTRICAL - Engine Sensors and Valves - Engine Oil
        Pressure (EOP) Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26511.2.5" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Oil Pressure (EOP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2651009" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="240px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 363. EOP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EOP sensor, a ceramic diaphragm sensor, detects engine oil pressure.</para>
        <para>The EOP signal is monitored by the ECM for operation of the instrument panel pressure gauge and optional
            EWPS.
        </para>
        <para>The EOP sensor is installed in the oil filter base.</para>
    </svcproc>
